      "description": "This table shows the fuel mix at different time steps across the entire ERCOT market region. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the fuel mix. The corresponding utc_timestamp invariant of daylight savings. The 'fuel_category' column includes the name of each type of technology in the ERCOT supply mix. In the 'fuel_category' column, 'WSL' value refers to wholesale storage load and 'Other' value refers to the battery storage discharge. The 'generation_mw' column contains the actual amount of energy produced by each technology in MW. The 'Is_day_ahead' column reflects if the data applies to the day-ahead market or if it is real-time data. The fuel mix data applies to the real-time market only."
    },
    {
      "name": "ercot_lmp",
      "description": "This table contains the locational marginal price of electricity in each hub and load zone within the ERCOT market. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the prices. The utc_timestamp, invariant of daylight savings, contains the utc timestamps associated with the price. The 'zone_name' column contains the zone names. The 'zone_type' column reflects if the corresponding zone is a generation zone/hub or if it is a load zone. The default prices to provide will be by generation zone/hub. However, if a user specifically asks for prices by load zone, the load zone type is used based on filters applied to the 'zone_type' column. The 'lmp' column contains the resultant energy prices in $/MWh. The 'Is_day_ahead' column reflects if the price data is for the day-ahead energy market or the real-time energy market."
    },
    {
      "name": "ercot_load",
      "description": "This table includes the actual real-time load across load regions in the ERCOT market. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the load data. The utc_timestamp, invariant of daylight savings, contains the utc timestamps associated with the load. The 'zone_name' column contains the zone names, while the 'region' column contains the names of the load regions. The 'load_mw' column contains the load data in MW. The 'Is_day_ahead' column reflects if the data applies to the day-ahead market or if it is real-time data."
    },
    {
      "name": "ercot_rtm_storage_awards",
      "description": "This table contains processed data from ERCOT's 60-day SCED disclosure report. The column descriptions are as follows. 'delivery_date' - contains time stamp with format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS, 'year'-contains corresponding year for data point, 'hour_ending'-contains hour ending for corresponding data point,'qse'-contains name of qualified scheduling entity, 'dme'-contains name of corresponding distribution metered entity,'resource_name'-contains name of the corresponding battery resource,'output schedule'-contains the corresponding output schedule for the battery asset from pre-real time market commitments which serves just as a reference point,'hsl'-contains high sustained limit parameters,'hasl'-contains high ancillary service limit parameters,'hdl'-contains high dispatch limit parameters, 'lsl'-contains low sustained limit parameters,'lasl'-contains low ancillary service limit parameters,'ldl'-contains low dispatch limit parameters,'base_point'-contains the real-time market dispatch instructions for energy only,'telemetered_new_output'-contains measured output from the battery asset includig real-time energy and ancillary service dispatch instructions,'ancillary_service_regup'-scheduled regup dispatch instructions,'ancillary_service_regdn'-scheduled regdn dispatch instructions,'ancillary_service_rrs'-scheduled rrs dispatch instructions,'ancillary_service_nsrs'-scheduled nsrs dispatch instructions','ancillary_service_ecrs'-scheduled ecrs dispatch instructions"
    },
    {
      "name": "regions",
      "description": "This table includes mappings of different load regions in the ERCOT market to zones. The name column contains the regions, while the zone column contains the hubs. The load regions apply to the load data by default and should only be used with the load table. If a user asks for prices by load region, this mapping table can be used to map the load regions to hubs, and then prices can be obtained based on the corresponding hub."
    },
    {
      "name": "zones",
      "description": "This table includes the names of each pricing hub in the ERCOT market. The 'name' column contains the hub names. The hubs provide geographical reference points for price data across different parts of the ERCOT market region."
    }
  ]
}",
